### 3. Converging GAN

##### Feature matching

In begin, $G$ gives poor smpl, so  $D$ close to 0 and lead $L_{GD}$ to infinite/gredient unstbl

Letting $f(x)$ denote activations on an layer of the $D$, our new objective for $G$ is:
$$
||E_{x\sim p_{data}}f(x)-E_{z\sim p_z(z)}f(G(Z))||^2
$$
##### Minibatch discrimination

minibatch discrimination is a strategy to avoid “ $G$ collapsing”  . 

By looking at multiple examples in simltly, and it states as follows:
$$
M_{i,b}=f(x_i) \times T\;\;\;\;\;\;\text{T is a weight mat}    \\
c_b(x_i,x_j)=\exp(-|| M_{i,b}-M_{j,b} ||)_{L_1} \\
o(x_i)_b=\sum_{j=1}^nc_b(x_i,x_j)\in R\\
o(x_i)=[o(x_i)_1,o(x_i)_2,\cdots,o(x_i)_n]
$$
And it looks like in graph as follows:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

The $D$ is therefore able to use the other examples in minibatch as side info. 

**NOTE**: Sample Version
$$
o =\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^n(\sigma_i)\\
\sigma_i=\sqrt{  \frac{1}{m-1}\sum_{j=1}^m( f(x_j)_i-\hat{f_i} )^2   }
$$

##### Historical averaging

Modifying player’s cost to include a term:
$$
|| \theta-\frac{1}{t}\sum_{i=1}^t\theta[i]\; ||^2
$$
where $θ[i]$ is the value of the parameters at past time $i$. 

##### One-sided label smoothin

Label smoothing replaces the 0 and 1 targets with smoothed values( 0.9-1,0-0.1).

We smooth only the positive labels to $α$, leaving negative labels set to 0.
